<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Setting the sound balance of a video and other settings]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=191&amp;p=4768#p4768"><![CDATA[
<blockquote><div><cite>zcorpan wrote:</cite><br /><blockquote><div><cite>pvk wrote:</cite>As soon as the player is getting in charge of the media element  (video or audio), one expect from it a bit more than just playing or pausing them<br />Here are some example of actions I would expect to see in the javascript API :<br /><br />setting the sound balance<br /></div></blockquote>What's the use case for this?</div></blockquote><br /><br />Sorry for the late follow up...<br /><br />Use case for setting the sound balance ?<br /><br />First a straight one : you are playing some stereoscopique sound and you want to adjust its balance (There must be some reason why this is possible on the QuickTime player, isn't it ?). You may for instance want to use that setting to reencode the sound on the server, correctly balanced.<br /><br />Then a very precise case I am indeed confronted with and for which I haven't yet found any solution : one of my client has media with two sound tracks associated with a video. One is the normal sound track and the second is the speaking clock used to index the video. The issue is that thoses two tracks are randomly organised on the left or right side of a stereoscopic media. At playing time, the user should be able to shut down the speaking clock track by setting the sound balance accordingly.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=308">pvk</a> — Mon Jan 05, 2009 10:21 am</p><hr />
