<title type="html"><![CDATA[Setting the sound balance of a video and other settings]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=191&amp;p=731#p731"><![CDATA[
As soon as the player is getting in charge of the media element  (video or audio), one expect from it a bit more than just playing or pausing them<br />Here are some example of actions I would expect to see in the javascript API :<br /><br />setting the sound balance<br />setting the sound volume<br />setting the rate (normal = 1, 0.2 = slow motion, 2 = twice faster, -1 = rewind, -10 = quite a fast rewind...)<br />going to any frame (setting the current frame trough a timecode like 00:03:26:12<br /> : hh:mn:ss:frameNumber)<br /><br />Similarly, one could expect to receive various event related to the beaviour of the player : when the end of the video is reched, when th eloading of the video is progressing or is done, when the video stated, paused or changed rate ....<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=308">pvk</a> — Wed Jun 11, 2008 1:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
